org.overture.ast.assistant

Interface IAstAssistantFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AstAssistantFactory

    public interface IAstAssistantFactory
    The IAstAssistantFactory defines the main interface for assistant factories. Assistants are responsible for providing generic functionality that is required on multiple occasions and that (for various reasons) cannot be implemented directly in the visitors.

    Factories are responsible for providing users with extensible access to the assistant functionality. Each module that needs assistants should create a factory and access a visitor by calling factory.createXAssistant where X is the node type that the functionality acts upon.

    All factories should subclass either this interface or one of its subclasses. These classes are in a straight hierarchy chain as follows: IAstAssistantFactory <- ITypeCheckerAssistantFactory <- *PluginLevelFactory

    By following this inheritance chain, at every level a single factory can provide all assistants. Extensions should hook into the hierarchy by subclassing their extension superclass, if one extist. Otherwise, subclass their Overture counterpart.
    Author:
    ldc, kel, gkanos, pvj
